# CODEOWNERS — who must review changes to protected paths.
#
# GitHub auto-requests review from the owner when a PR touches a matching path.
# ENFORCEMENT requires branch protection → "Require review from Code Owners"
# (see docs: repo Settings → Branches → main). Without that, this only *requests*.
#
# Goal for this template: LO authors add content freely (lo-config/, fixtures,
# new LO JSON) but cannot silently change the design system, config schemas,
# core engine wiring, or the build/CI/guard setup that keeps every course consistent.

# Everything defaults to the maintainer unless a more specific rule below wins.
*                       @pedbad

# --- Design system: tokens, theme, global CSS (drift here breaks every course) ---
/src/styles/            @pedbad

# --- Config + schemas: the LO/exercise contract and course config ---
/src/config/            @pedbad

# --- Core engine plumbing: registry + shared scaffold (not individual engines) ---
/src/exercises/lazyRegistry.ts   @pedbad
/src/exercises/lib/              @pedbad

# --- Build, tooling, CI, and the TDD-guard wiring ---
/.github/               @pedbad
/vite.config.ts         @pedbad
/package.json           @pedbad
/bun.lock               @pedbad
/tsconfig*.json         @pedbad
/eslint.config.js       @pedbad
/prettier.config.mjs    @pedbad
/.stylelintrc*          @pedbad
/.claude/settings.json  @pedbad

# --- Specs + canonical process docs (the source of truth authors build against) ---
/docs/specs/            @pedbad
